The L Word.description: This trailblazing series follows the tangled lives and ever-changing relationships among a close-knit group of lesbians who call Los Angeles home.

The Lady in Dignity.description: The wife of a corporate heir finds her luxurious life overturned by a mysterious woman who joins the household as a caregiver for her father-in-law.

The Liar.description: At the CARE detective agency, investigators see a lot of action but must always keep their cases secret, even when it affects their personal lives.

The Lizzie Borden Chronicles.description: Exonerated in the murder of her father and stepmother, Lizzie Borden takes on crime lords, detectives and other foes as she savors her new infamy.

The Making of Frozen Planet.description: Documentary crew members brave Earth's most frigid regions to capture the majesty and mystery found in the chillier side of the animal kingdom.

The Messengers.description: A group of strangers who are killed by a mysterious object soon come back to life and learn they have been chosen to prevent the apocalypse.

The Mind of a Chef.description: Producer and narrator Anthony Bourdain explores the creative processes of international celebrity chefs to learn what fuels their culinary artistry.

The Minimighty Kids.description: Some have big feet or a sniffly nose, others are clumsy or too sweaty – but these kids soon discover their mini problems can become superpowers.

The Ministry of Time.description: Three officers from different eras work for a secret agency guarding Spain's past from time-traveling intruders trying to manipulate history.

The Mortified Guide.description: Brave people get onstage to read hilarious and humiliating tales of gawky teenage love, family dysfunction and other stories from their younger years.

The Most Beautiful Hands of Delhi.description: A stalled career, failed marriage and receding hairline drive a middle-aged Swedish man to try to revitalize his life by visiting India.

The Murder Detectives.description: This series tracks the ups and downs of an 18-month investigation into the 2014 stabbing murder of teenager Nicholas Robinson in Bristol, England.

The Netflix Afterparty.description: Hosts David Spade, Fortune Feimster and London Hughes welcome guests from the newest and biggest Netflix titles for fun conversations, skits and more.

The Nineties.description: This U.S.-focused series dives into the cultural and political changes that swept the last decade of the 20th century. Executive produced by Tom Hanks.

The Office (U.S.).description: This hit comedy chronicles the foibles of disgruntled office workers – led by deluded boss Michael Scott – at the Dunder Mifflin paper company.

The Pyramid Code.description: How was the scientific understanding of the ancients so advanced? A team of experts answers this and other questions in this fascinating series.

The Rap Game.description: Young lyricists between the ages of 12 and 16 compete for a chance to sign to Jermaine Dupri's label while being mentored by hip-hop and R&B's finest.

The Real Football Factories.description: Examine the troubling history of football hooliganism and hear from real hooligans about their bitter rivalries and rowdiest brawls.

The Returned.description: On returning home and finding they're believed to be dead, a collection of near-strangers from the same village try to find a reason for their plight.

The Road to Calvary.description: Swept up in political unrest during World War I, two sisters in St. Petersburg cope with turbulent romances as Russian history is made around them.

The Seventies.description: This series examines 1970s America, focusing on the major political and historical landmarks of the decade and the cultural response to those events.

The Sniffer.description: An extraordinary sense of smell gives a crime investigator unique insight into solving mysteries, but his gift takes a toll on his personal life.

The Story of God with Morgan Freeman.description: Host Morgan Freeman explores religion's role in human history, how our beliefs connect us and possible answers to life's million-dollar questions.

The Story of Us with Morgan Freeman.description: Explore the forces of love, belief, power, war, peace, rebellion and freedom in this series about the ties that bind – and destroy – humanity.

The Super Mario Bros. Super Show!.description: Mixing live action and animation, this classic series brought the beloved Super Mario Bros. video game characters to television screens everywhere.

The Traffickers.description: In this hard-hitting series, journalist Nelufar Hedayat travels the globe to expose an array of black markets, from guns and gold to human body parts.

The Tudors.description: All the splendor and scandal of England's 16th-century royal court comes to life in this series that follows notorious Tudor monarch Henry VIII.

The Twilight Zone (Original Series).description: Hosted by creator Rod Serling, this groundbreaking anthology series presents tales of the supernatural that are often tinged with social commentary.

The Underwear.description: Virtual and real worlds collide as a group of teenagers who are grappling with matters of the heart cross paths in a cafe and on an anonymous website.

The Universe.description: Discover the secrets of the universe in this series that pairs animation with insights on distant planets, black holes and other celestial marvels.

The Vietnam War: A Film by Ken Burns and.description: Ken Burns presents an epic 10-part, 18-hour chronicle of the Vietnam War, featuring the soldiers, protesters, politicians and families that lived it.

The War: A Film by Ken Burns and Lynn No.description: A seven-part series brings World War II to life through the harrowing personal accounts of soldiers and others from "typical" American towns.

The West Wing.description: This powerful political epic chronicles the triumphs and travails of White House senior staff under the administration of President Josiah Bartlet.

The Womanizer.description: Libertine He-jie finds himself torn between the lovely Amanda and fiery Xiao-qian. But now he faces a new problem: arrogant rival suitor Cheng-en.

The Year of Happiness and Love.description: Jiang Chen-bo is a loser without prospects for success, until a surprise promotion becomes the catalyst for his entire family's upturn in fortune.

ThirTEEN Terrors.description: A group of teens searches for the dark truth behind their school's mysterious and brutal history.

This Is My Love.description: A renowned actor who is still pining over the loss of his first real love writes an autobiography about his memories of her, hoping to reconnect.

Tientsin Mystic.description: In an otherworldly river town, a policeman follows the trail of a sinister force to save his community from deadly spells.

Timeless Season.description: A decade after college, a wake reunites five female friends struggling with illness, infidelity, toxic in-laws, spousal abuse and other life issues.

Timeline.description: Firsthand accounts, re-enactments and computer-generated graphics retell in detail Thailand's biggest news stories from the past.

Tip the Mouse.description: In his tiny meadow village, curious little mouse Tip enjoys fun and adventure while learning about the world with his furry friends and family.

Toast of London.description: After a divorce and fatal career move, a classically trained British stage actor navigates single life with his odd roommate and takes on horrid jobs.

Tobot.description: They’re robots that can transform into cars – and the Tobots are committed to fighting villains to protect the city and root out crime.

Top 10 Secrets and Mysteries.description: This series investigates mysteries that persistently elude scientific explanation, such as mythical creatures, UFOs, sacred sites and more.

Top Grier.description: Social media star Hayes Grier returns to North Carolina for a reality series packed with action sports, pranks and romantic escapades.

Towies.description: Australia's toughest tow truck operators work to keep Queensland's streets clear of overturned semis and other automotive disasters.

Trotsky.description: The complex historical figure of Leon Trotsky comes to life in this epic biography that depicts the tumultuous life of the Russian revolutionary.

Twin Peaks.description: "Who killed Laura Palmer?" is the question on everyone's lips in a secretive small town, but as an eccentric FBI agent learns, the answer isn't easy.

Twirlywoos.description: The colorful and curious family of Twirlywoos bounces around their boat and visits new places, turning learning into adventures wherever they land.

Ugly Duckling.description: Young women face up to their insecurities and circumstances, finding love and laughs along the way. Featuring a different storyline every season.

V.R. Troopers.description: Three friends who study martial arts find themselves defending humanity from a criminal mastermind and his invading army from another dimension.

ViR: The Robot Boy.description: Humanoid robot boy ViR lives with his inventor, Dr. Prem Sahay, and, with his best friends, is always ready to use his superpowers to save the day.

Vroomiz.description: For these half-car, half-animal friends, each day in Zippy City is a chance to have fun, be creative and use teamwork to solve difficult problems.

Wake Up.description: After taking the blame for a patient death, an anesthesiologist battling psychiatric trauma fights to stay afloat in the corrupt hospital system.

Wartime Portraits.description: Part live-action and part animation, this visually inventive series offers striking portrayals of some of the unsung heroes of World War II.

Weeds.description: A suburban mother starts selling marijuana to her affluent neighbors so she can maintain her comfortable lifestyle after her husband's sudden death.

Weird Wonders of the World.description: From animal oddities and bizarre science to medical marvels, scientists and experts examine some of the world's strangest mysteries and phenomena.

What Happens to My Family.description: A naïve young woman goes to Istanbul to meet the now-grown boy who jokingly promised to marry her in 11 years after she saved his life as a child.

What Is Love?.description: A 32-year-old romantic looking for a long-term, monogamous relationship meets a handsome bad boy who only believes in one-night stands.

When Calls the Heart.description: Leaving behind her upper-crust city roots, a woman journeys west in the early 1900s to become a teacher in a small Canadian mining community.

Who's the One.description: A doctor performs plastic surgery on a fat man who's been jilted, and continues his transformation by turning him into a handsome, desirable man.

Wild Alaska.description: The natural bounty of Alaska sustains its diverse species through extreme weather conditions in three seasons, each with its rewards and challenges.

Wild Arabia.description: The widely varied geology and dramatic landscapes in the continental crossroads of Arabia harbors a rich history and an abundance of wildlife.

Winsanity.description: Actor Donald Faison hosts this game show in which contestants must arrange numerical-based trivia tidbits from largest to smallest for various prizes.

Winter Sun.description: Years after ruthless businessmen kill his father and order the death of his twin brother, a modest fisherman adopts a new persona to exact revenge.

Women Behind Bars.description: This reality series recounts true stories of women who have been convicted for murder, including an in-depth examination of each crime.

World's Busiest Cities.description: From Moscow to Mexico City, three BBC journalists delve into the inner workings of some of the most burgeoning metropolises on Earth.

Yeh Meri Family.description: In the summer of 1998, middle child Harshu balances school, family, friendship and other challenges of growing up.

Yo-Kai Watch.description: Nate frees a mythical being trapped in a magic capsule, and the two new friends have adventures with all sorts of troublesome supernatural creatures.

Yoko.description: Friends Mai, Oto and Vik's games at the park become magical adventures, thanks to Yoko, who can turn playgrounds into spaceships and camping sites.

YOM.description: With the mind of a human being, and the body of whichever animal he chooses to be, a young boy protects the world from danger.

Yu-Gi-Oh! Arc-V.description: Now that he's discovered the Pendulum Summoning technique, Yuya's dream of becoming the greatest "dueltainer" is in reach – but it won't be easy!

Yunus Emre.description: During the Mongol invasions, Yunus Emre leaves his home to travel across the Ottoman Empire, defying hardships and temptations to become a dervish.

Zak Storm.description: Teen surfer Zak Storm is mysteriously transported to the Bermuda Triangle, where he becomes the captain of a magical ship full of misfits.

Zindagi Gulzar Hai.description: Strong-willed, middle-class Kashaf and carefree, wealthy Zaroon meet in college, but before love can take root, they each have some growing up to do.

Zombie Dumb.description: While living alone in a spooky town, a young girl befriends a motley crew of zombie children with diverse personalities.
